{"questionId":"8899380","questionHtml":"<p>Four identical resistors, each of resistance <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>R</mi></math>, are connected as shown.</p>\n<p><img style=\"display:block;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;\" src=\"__IMG__/7b587730616bd25a581b55f152f942736b71b5a1.png\"></p>\n<p>What is the effective resistance between P and Q?</p>\n<p><br>A.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>R</mi></mrow><mn>4</mn></mfrac></math></p>\n<p>B.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>R</mi></math></p>\n<p>C.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mn>4</mn><mi>R</mi></mrow><mn>3</mn></mfrac></math></p>\n<p>D.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>4</mn><mi>R</mi></math></p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>A</p>","meta":{"questionId":"8899380","referenceCode":"SPM.1A.SL.TZ0.10","subjectId":"59-dp-physics-first-assessment-2025","title":"Four identical resistors, each of resistance R, are connected as shown. What is the effective resistance between P and Q? A. 3R4 B. R C. 4R3 D. 4R","paper":"1A","level":"SL","questionNumber":"10","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["B. The particulate nature of matter","B. The particulate nature of matter","B.5 Current and circuits"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}